      • getParcelLikeFrenchWithSimulatedFileds

        public static org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection getParcelLikeFrenchWithSimulatedFileds(org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection sfc)
                                                                                               throws java.io.IOException
        This method returns the parcels of a given collection that have been simulated. It selects the parcels if the length of the filed value for the SECTION information is upper than 2 (French Parcel have a two letters section, and Parcel Manager creates longer section names) Other methods can be set to determine if a parcel has been simulated.
        Parameters:
        sfc - Parcel collection to sort
        Returns:
        The parcel SimpleFeatureCollection with only the simulated parcels
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • isParcelLikeFrenchHasSimulatedFileds

        public static boolean isParcelLikeFrenchHasSimulatedFileds(org.opengis.feature.simple.SimpleFeature feature)
        This method allows to determine if a parcel has been simulated. It looks if the length of filed value for the SECTION information is upper than 2 (French Parcel have a two letters section, and Parcel Manager creates longer section names). Other methods can be set to determine if a parcel has been simulated.
        Parameters:
        feature - : SimpleFeature parcel
        Returns:
        True if the parcel section looks like it has been simulated.
